		<paragraph indent="0" tabs="" style="normal" height="0" width="400" y="+0" x="12" type="text"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">The quickest way to tackle this exercise is to decide which are the key words in the questions and then skim to find those same words, or synonyms, in the passage. Once you've found them, read the whole sentence carefully. Remember, just because one of the choices contains words from the passage doesn't mean that it will be correct. And don't forget, you have to choose two correct options for each question.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
